Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.39,0:00:04.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Invited by Hattori Heiji and Toyama Kazuha,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.31,0:00:06.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran and I came to Yadori Village in Shizuoka
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.02,0:00:10.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,to help unearth Tokugawa's buried treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.52,0:00:16.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that night, the legendary \Nmonster known as the Nue appeared,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.82,0:00:18.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and Someji Yasukatsu-san was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.10,0:00:25.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Tanzawa Michiki-san was also \Nmurdered in his hotel room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.20,0:00:27.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.20,0:00:29.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.63,0:00:33.32,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The police told you to stay inside the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.32,0:00:36.47,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but we're worried about the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.71,0:00:39.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When the nue's cry sounded earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.73,0:00:43.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,we heard him barking and \Nscratching at the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.71,0:00:48.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, when we \Nfirst heard the nue's cry...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.34,0:00:50.27,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He was barking then, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.71,0:00:54.18,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But when the monster appeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.70,0:00:56.28,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.36,0:00:58.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.48,0:01:01.54,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.87,0:01:07.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Curtains rise as the headliner appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.84,0:01:09.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He beautifully dances his \Nmystery-solving steps!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.35,0:01:13.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After solving the mystery of the \NNue, what will Heiji say to Kazuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.18,0:01:15.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.92,0:01:18.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.02,0:01:20.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.99,0:03:06.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,1)}Conan and Heiji's Nue Legend \N(Resolution Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.76,0:03:05.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Conan and Heiji's Nue \NLegend, Resolution Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:09.50,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.78,0:03:11.93,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,We brought what you asked for.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.67,0:03:17.04,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Three sets of sheets from an \Nunused room, a deck brush,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.04,0:03:18.54,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,a mop, and a toolbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.04,0:03:23.39,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's a cardboard box and the \Nspray used to remodel the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.81,0:03:28.04,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,We also borrowed a permanent marker \Nand sewing set from Masuko-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:30.89,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,and some glue and a knife from Tsurumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.24,0:03:32.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.90,0:03:34.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.02,0:03:35.15,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:38.96,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,In the desk drawer of the\Nroom Ran and I moved into
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.96,0:03:41.20,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,there was an old photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:46.47,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the excavation \Nteam from sixteen years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.47,0:03:47.70,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.70,0:03:50.75,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,And it may be our imagination,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.75,0:03:54.08,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,but the foreigner in the middle of the photo
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.74,0:03:57.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}kind of looks like Tsurumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:58.09,Hajime,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Tsurumi Hajime (22) \NDocumentary Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.79,0:03:59.87,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.34,0:04:04.80,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you going to \Nmake with all this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:07.22,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.64,0:04:09.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to summon...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.36,0:04:11.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...that monster again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.99,0:04:13.64,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.37,0:04:18.90,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What is Heiji thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.80,0:04:23.46,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't feel romantic at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.46,0:04:24.66,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.24,0:04:27.02,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.09,0:04:32.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up, Kudo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:34.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise the sun will rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.96,0:04:38.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the trick's too obvious \Nunless it's done at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.67,0:04:39.50,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.36,0:04:42.30,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.05,0:04:48.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there isn't some other reason you \Ndon't want the sun to rise yet, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.77,0:04:51.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,N-Not especially.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.31,0:04:56.06,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.93,0:04:58.48,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.82,0:05:01.48,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,You woke me up while I was fast asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.04,0:05:05.94,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's only four in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.94,0:05:09.88,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But Hattori-sama asked me to gather \Neveryone in front of the hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.82,0:05:12.45,Densuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Takekuma Densuke (58) \NYadori Village Mayor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.88,0:05:12.45,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}...because he discovered \Nthe identity of the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.70,0:05:14.38,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,The identity of the nue?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.38,0:05:15.58,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.01,0:05:20.91,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Come to think of it, the forensics \Nteam and my men were sneaking around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.79,0:05:22.96,Fumie,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(25,1)}Masuko Fumie (46) \NAuthor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.91,0:05:22.96,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Without telling you what they were doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.24,0:05:24.41,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.48,0:05:26.86,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-Isn't that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.86,0:05:27.89,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.89,0:05:29.89,Danger,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay Out \NDanger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.24,0:05:38.82,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It's burning just like it was \Nwhen the monster appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.82,0:05:41.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There's even a sign there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.72,0:05:49.76,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What is this eerie sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.05,0:05:51.66,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.24,0:05:59.42,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,It's the nue's cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:11.05,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji, where are you?! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.50,0:06:13.43,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.43,0:06:16.09,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Where's here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.59,0:06:18.03,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.66,0:06:22.36,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.94,0:06:29.36,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:34.03,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Heiji, you...g-grew?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.30,0:06:37.66,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,No, dummy. Come over here \Nand take a closer look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.00,0:06:41.35,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,B-But standing in front of you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.35,0:06:43.54,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There's a black monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:46.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this isn't a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.07,0:06:47.97,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.61,0:06:52.93,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's an ordinary dog wearing a bear skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.18,0:06:54.27,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:06:58.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I found this skin in the back of a closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:02.91,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Look. There's even a snake \Ntail attached to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.37,0:07:06.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, come over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.52,0:07:08.57,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then you'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.86,0:07:11.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.16,0:07:14.10,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,T-Try not to step on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.40,0:07:18.20,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.40,0:07:19.62,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.84,0:07:22.22,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,No way. What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.22,0:07:24.13,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.52,0:07:26.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We sewed some sheets together,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.48,0:07:29.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,drew some windows on them \Nin extreme perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.25,0:07:31.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and hung it from the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.88,0:07:35.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,For the parts sticking out, we stuck \Npieces of cardboard to the sheets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.38,0:07:38.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and spray painted them the \Nsame color as the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.97,0:07:43.60,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And since that tree's in the \Nway, you can't see the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.12,0:07:48.26,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When there's smoke in the air, you \Ncan't see the trees behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.26,0:07:52.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, in the darkness of \Nnight, it's no wonder we were fooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:57.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Officers, you can put out the fire now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.72,0:07:58.91,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.80,0:08:07.73,DCItalic,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,So the forensics team and my men
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.73,0:08:10.42,DCItalic,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,were secretly helping him \Nput together this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.43,0:08:14.72,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The finishing touch is this sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.84,0:08:20.58,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,They trained the dog to \Ncarry away this little sign
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:24.02,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,when he heard the nue's cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.47,0:08:29.05,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and left the real sign with giant teeth marks
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.05,0:08:31.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,next to Someji-san's body,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.71,0:08:35.61,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,so it'd look like a giant \Nmonster killed Someji-san
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:40.33,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and disappeared, leaving the sign behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.72,0:08:42.27,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Remember how this dog barked
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:46.04,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,when he heard the nue's cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.04,0:08:50.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He was barking because he wanted \Nto go to the sign, but couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.02,0:08:55.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The nue's cry could have \Nbeen produced the first
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.10,0:08:59.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,or second time using a \Ncell phone or something...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.11,0:09:03.70,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,But we heard its cry when \NTanzawa-san was poisoned, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.70,0:09:07.35,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Hadn't you taken everything we \Ncould've used to make any sound then?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.85,0:09:09.96,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,How did they create that cry?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.96,0:09:11.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's this sound, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.93,0:09:17.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you fill a wineglass with water
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.39,0:09:21.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and trace the edge of the \Nglass with a moist finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:25.90,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen that on TV before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.90,0:09:26.87,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.56,0:09:31.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the only person who could've \Nhung the cloth painted
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:32.75,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,with windows from that \Nspot and made that sound
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.37,0:09:37.80,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,is the person staying in that room \Non the second floor who asked
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:41.75,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,for wine to be sent to their room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.08,0:09:53.65,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It was you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.88,0:09:59.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Masuko Fumie-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.67,0:10:01.98,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,As an art school graduate,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.98,0:10:05.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,you'd be able to draw realistic \Nlooking windows on the cloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:09.29,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And when we chased the monster \Naround the back of the hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.29,0:10:11.29,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,since this area was burning,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:14.80,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,you could've erased the evidence \Nby setting the cloth on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:18.68,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We did find its burnt remains, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.68,0:10:22.85,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,But when did she paint \Nthose windows on the cloth?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.85,0:10:27.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She probably painted them beforehand \Nand hid it in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.62,0:10:29.45,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Beforehand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.45,0:10:33.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was coming here occasionally \Nto feed the dog, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.75,0:10:36.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably Masuko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.19,0:10:40.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She had to train the dog to pull \Nthe sign out of the ground, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.45,0:10:45.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Masuko-san may have planted this tree \Nfor the sake of this trick, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.18,0:10:50.46,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the second time the grass \Ncaught fire, she was in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.83,0:10:52.90,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,How did she start the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.45,0:10:55.13,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Using metallic sodium.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.13,0:10:57.71,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,What? Metallic sodium?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.26,0:11:02.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you wrap it in something flammable \Nlike paper or grass and pour water on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.00,0:11:05.33,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,it becomes extremely hot and catches fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.82,0:11:09.98,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When we put out the first \Nfire, Masuko-san had a bucket.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.41,0:11:13.11,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If she had the sodium in the bucket,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:16.38,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,she could have faked putting out the fire and \Nstrewn it over the grass in front of the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.18,0:11:20.41,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,B-But how did she pour water on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.41,0:11:22.66,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You said it yourself, Mr. Mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.66,0:11:24.07,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When the grass caught fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.07,0:11:27.49,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,you heard the sound of a carbonated \Nbeverage being opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.84,0:11:30.02,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,She opened a hole in the wine cork
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.02,0:11:33.12,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and stuck a ball point pen \Ntube emptied of ink in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.12,0:11:36.75,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then she wrapped tape around the cork
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.75,0:11:40.38,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,so it would fit perfectly \Nin the soda water bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:44.39,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,By shaking the bottle, she was able \Nto shoot water at a distant target.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.39,0:11:47.14,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Hah, shoot water at a distant target?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.50,0:11:49.54,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.36,0:11:51.09,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:52.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.29,0:11:53.56,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.56,0:11:54.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.08,0:11:58.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to make the \Nsame thing using the spare
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.40,0:12:01.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,bottle of soda water and \Nwine cork the mayor bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.13,0:12:05.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And I used the same tape \Nand pen Masuko-san had.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.07,0:12:11.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, if you point the bottle \Nupwards and release your finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.80,0:12:14.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,See? It easily reaches the window above.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.14,0:12:17.14,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The window above?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.14,0:12:21.01,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Then Tanzawa-san was poisoned using...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.01,0:12:22.05,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.35,0:12:26.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,By attaching a two-pronged \Npoison dart to the cork
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.56,0:12:30.60,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and shaking the bottle while holding \Nit in place with her finger,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.60,0:12:34.02,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,she was able to poison Tanzawa-san \Nby releasing her finger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.02,0:12:36.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,when he stuck his head out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.57,0:12:41.14,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And by attaching a string to the poison \Ndart, she was able to quickly retrieve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.02,0:12:45.82,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, here's what you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:51.08,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,After hanging the cloth painted with \Nwindows from your second story room,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.34,0:12:55.92,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,you invited Someji-san outside with a \Nletter or something and murdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.92,0:12:57.54,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You cut claw marks into his back,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.54,0:13:02.23,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,left the sign with large \Nteeth marks next to the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.23,0:13:05.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,switched the real sign \Nout for the little one,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.17,0:13:09.47,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,poured kerosene over the grass in front \Nof the hotel, and set it on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.11,0:13:13.50,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When everyone came outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.50,0:13:16.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,you used your phone to produce the nue's cry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.28,0:13:18.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,calling this dog wearing the bear skin,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.96,0:13:22.86,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,who took the sign just like you trained him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.86,0:13:25.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,went around the back of the \Nhotel, and headed back inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.36,0:13:31.11,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,While pretending to put out the fire, you \Nscattered metallic sodium in front of the hotel
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.11,0:13:33.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and sprayed water on it \Nwithout spraying it on us,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:36.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,while we were keeping watch outside, \Nto ignite the metallic sodium.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.17,0:13:41.02,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When Tanzawa-san stuck his head out \Nof his window to look at the fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:42.44,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,you poisoned him using the dart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.90,0:13:45.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The first man was killed by a \Ntiger, and the second by a snake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.28,0:13:48.47,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You made it seem as though both of \Nthem had been killed by the nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.72,0:13:53.47,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You no doubt threw the knife you \Nused to kill Someji-san in the lake,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.47,0:13:58.14,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,but if forensics hasn't found the \Ndart you used to kill Tanzawa-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.14,0:14:02.20,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,it's probably still inside \Nthe pens you have on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.66,0:14:05.98,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You could've made a two-pronged dart
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.98,0:14:07.99,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,by tying sewing needles to a toothpick.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.64,0:14:14.54,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're lucky the needles \Nstruck Tanzawa-san's chin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.47,0:14:19.00,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.20,0:14:19.83,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:20.75,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.31,0:14:23.07,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It was 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.44,0:14:26.54,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,I practiced countless \Ntimes so I could hit him,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.54,0:14:29.26,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,no matter where he stuck his head out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.47,0:14:32.60,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You admit to killing them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:36.77,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.78,0:14:44.67,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Because they let him die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.96,0:14:51.61,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Member of the excavation \Nteam and my husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.89,0:14:54.91,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Charles Abel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.13,0:15:02.93,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,W-Were they on the excavation team, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.93,0:15:03.68,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.10,0:15:05.72,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,When the cave-in occurred,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:07.92,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,they left my husband behind
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:11.18,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,and fled even though he was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.41,0:15:14.70,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,But they couldn't have helped it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.78,0:15:21.19,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,He wrote the name of a \Nmonster on a piece of paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.66,0:15:24.17,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not nue.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.17,0:15:26.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's "tetsuno" (metal), isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.92,0:15:27.86,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.58,0:15:34.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Charles was trying to write \Nthat he found a metal hairpin,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:38.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but as a foreigner he'd \Nnever seen one before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.19,0:15:40.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,After writing the word "metal,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.06,0:15:43.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he meant to show the team the hairpin
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.74,0:15:46.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the piece of paper \Nto ask them what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.88,0:15:49.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since he wrote the word slowly \Nusing a permanent marker,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.87,0:15:52.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the ink bled through,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.46,0:15:56.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,making the team think he \Nwrote "n-u-e" instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.19,0:15:58.32,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.76,0:16:03.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You used that misunderstanding \Nto bring them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.58,0:16:09.32,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You wrote in your letter that Charles \Nmay have found metal jars instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:10.65,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Metal jars?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.02,0:16:12.44,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.83,0:16:16.54,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,"In the morning and evening sun, two thousand \Njars glitter with a thousand golden coins"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.02,0:16:20.66,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,is how the nursery song goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.66,0:16:24.54,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,A jar containing a thousand golden \Ncoins would make a fine treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.54,0:16:28.55,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And the two of them came, \Ndrawn by that possibility,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:31.36,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,without realizing they'd be murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:32.23,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.65,0:16:35.54,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,I planned to forgive them \Nif they didn't come,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.02,0:16:39.06,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,but they shamelessly came like \Nthe miserable wretches they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.23,0:16:42.70,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You invited a detective so \Nhe'd testify that the monster
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.70,0:16:44.38,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,actually exists and a young woman
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.38,0:16:46.94,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,so she'd be frightened when \Nshe found the creepy notebook
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.94,0:16:51.82,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the foreigner used to practice his hiragana.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.15,0:16:55.19,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You predicted that Tanzawa-san \Nwould offer to trade rooms
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.19,0:17:00.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,with the girl when she became frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.74,0:17:02.99,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,A room containing Charles' possessions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:06.83,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,may have held some clue to the metal jars.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.04,0:17:10.22,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then why'd she invite me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.22,0:17:12.50,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,when I had nothing to do with any of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.50,0:17:18.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because Masuko-san's your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.76,0:17:19.63,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.20,0:17:25.45,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted her son to watch \Nas she avenged his father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.98,0:17:29.86,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The dog probably likes you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.86,0:17:34.03,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,because he sees his dead owner in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.50,0:17:38.78,DCMain,HAJIME,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.31,0:17:42.29,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot. Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.90,0:17:45.84,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,I invited you for fun
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.84,0:17:48.28,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,after reading one of your awful articles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.13,0:17:58.51,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,So you'd better write a \Nbetter one this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:04.44,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,About the idiot woman who got \Na taste of her own medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.44,0:18:06.23,DCMain,FUMIE,0000,0000,0000,,when she tried to use a monster legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.32,0:18:16.54,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like the legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.54,0:18:17.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.16,0:18:19.81,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,According to one theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.81,0:18:24.37,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,the nue was the mother of Minamoto Yorimasa,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:29.32,DCMain,DENSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,who transformed into the beast \Nso her son could slay it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.16,0:20:00.34,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.77,0:20:03.81,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that you, Ran-san and Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.81,0:20:05.52,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.52,0:20:07.76,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,There was a major case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.21,0:20:09.71,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.71,0:20:12.60,DCMain,YOKOMIZO,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you? Where are you, Mori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.82,0:20:12.60,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.16,0:20:15.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You just noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.61,0:20:16.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.84,0:20:17.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.78,0:20:19.62,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen Kazuha-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.62,0:20:24.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She headed towards Kurogane \NLake with Heiji-niichan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:29.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I think you should \Nleave them alone for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.44,0:20:31.71,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,"Watch how I do things."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.71,0:20:33.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He said something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.38,0:20:34.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.56,0:20:46.55,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you bring me here, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.96,0:20:50.94,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,If you're planning to show me another \Nweird monster, give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.94,0:20:52.35,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,No, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.18,0:20:56.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll only say it once, so listen closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.52,0:21:09.24,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.58,0:21:10.44,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.36,0:21:29.86,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,The morning sun turned the \Nsurface of the lake gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.53,0:21:34.18,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. That's what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.46,0:21:36.34,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.34,0:21:39.71,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,"In the morning and evening sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.71,0:21:43.15,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,two thousand jars glitter with \Na thousand golden coins."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.15,0:21:45.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The name Kurogane refers to the metal jars.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.52,0:21:47.70,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the lake \Nitself is a metal jar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.02,0:21:52.20,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,When the light from the rising and setting \Nsun strikes the lake, it turns gold,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.20,0:21:56.46,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and the waves look like coins \Nscattered across the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.71,0:21:59.08,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.45,0:22:03.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not what I came to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.52,0:22:04.22,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.60,0:22:13.50,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't realize it until the \Nincident at the Ebisu Bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.18,0:22:16.92,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.87,0:22:19.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,have...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.09,0:22:23.56,DCMain,SOLDIER 2,0000,0000,0000,,Evacuate the civilians to a safe area!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.62,0:22:22.41,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.56,0:22:25.00,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.68,0:22:28.78,DCMain,SOLDIER 3,0000,0000,0000,,Operation Capture the Nue begins now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.93,0:22:33.58,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The self-defense force?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.85,0:22:35.83,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-They actually came!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.56,0:22:45.34,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If they did come, I guess it \Nwould be the Hamamatsu ADSF.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.60,0:22:48.80,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,S-So, what were you going to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.34,0:22:53.40,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.40,0:22:57.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I was just going to say that gruel does \Ntaste better when you mix the egg into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.14,0:22:59.24,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.24,0:23:02.11,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Gruel always tastes better when you mix it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.48,0:23:07.11,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.18,0:23:11.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What did Hattori-kun say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.94,0:23:15.76,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji says it tastes better \Nwhen you mix the egg in.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.16,0:23:18.75,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.96,0:23:20.76,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you so!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.26,0:23:32.76,Headlines,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Author Masuko Fumie Arrested For Murder \NHigh School Detective Hattori \NHeiji Finds The Truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.74,0:23:32.76,DCMain,MOMIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. Looks like you're \Nmaking quite the splash.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.46,0:23:35.20,DCMain,MOMIJI,0000,0000,0000,,My future...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.81,0:23:38.79,DCMain,MOMIJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.72,0:23:41.98,Momoji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Ooka Momoji (17) \NKyoto Senshin High School \NSecond-Year
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.98,0:24:09.01,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.14,0:23:49.88,DCMain,WOMAN 1,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.88,0:23:52.34,DCMain,WOMAN 2,0000,0000,0000,,Could something bad be happening again?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.98,0:23:56.43,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Buddha is warning the living
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.43,0:23:59.29,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,that misfortune is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.29,0:24:02.17,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing for a detective \Nto involve himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.81,0:24:05.13,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
